msItem.note:
Similar to that contained in the Vatican manuscript, edited by Count Miniscalchi Erizzo(
                    Evangeliarium Hierosolymitanum ex sCod. Vat.. Palaestino etc., Verona, 1801—64
                  ). See below,Part 5. An edition of these fragments is in the course of preparation of Dr. Land.

physDesc.p:
Vellum leaves, about 9 5/8 in. by 8.
              These leaves are palimpsest (see Add. 14,664, foll, 1-17, 20, 21
                ), with the exception of foll. 1, 2, 8, 20, and 21;
              Foll. 4, 6, 10, and 15, are re-written on one side only.
